  "elapsed_s": 69.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And with my aunt and uncles around in the city, with whom we could meet less and less, we decided that we are not taking that route.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We don't even try it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was rather dubious if it would help anyhow.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was just simply said that we are not doing it and be what it will be.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As far as family or--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Just my mother and father and, and eventually, it happened after I was already rounded up with my father and when, when Wallenberg's activities-- which is well-known nowadays, from history and, and from international recognition for his activities.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Wallenberg was an emissary of the Swedish government in Hungary, trying to mediate for the-- saving of Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my mother and my father eventually and my aunt and my cousin, a girl, and my grandmother were in one of these defended homes of this-- defended homes, [NON-ENGLISH] houses, [NON-ENGLISH] from under the protectorate of the Swedish or other foreign embassies.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I-- we had no contact with family members, really at all, during the days when we were in that Jewish house.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The protected house.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I never was part of it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, there were some vague information around that people were able to get this protectorates and having papers that you are under the [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] protection of the Swedish or, or Swiss government.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that means that you are on the quota to eventually lead immigration papers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they would let you into Sweden or Switzerland or whatever else, another one or two countries participated, but mostly Sweden.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had no way to know how it happens, and it wasn't urgent.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were in that house, and we didn't know what the-- what they would protect us from.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
